{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id60317d42-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1211"},"text":"§ 1211.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Office of Surface Mining Reclamation and Enforcement","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id60317d43-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Establishment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"There is established in the Department of the Interior, the Office of Surface Mining Reclamation and Enforcement (hereinafter referred to as the “Office”).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id60317d44-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Appointment, compensation, duties, etc., of Director; employees","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Office shall have a Director who shall be appointed by the President, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate, and shall be compensated at the rate provided for level V of the Executive Schedule under section 5315 ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002059"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002059"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be section “5316”."}],"tail":" of title 5, and such other employees as may be required. Pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5108"},"text":"section 5108 of title 5","children":[],"tail":", and after consultation with the Secretary, the Director of the Office of Personnel Management shall determine the necessary number of positions in general schedule employees in grade 16, 17, and 18 to perform functions of this subchapter and shall allocate such positions to the Secretary. The Director shall have the responsibilities provided under subsection (c) of this section and those duties and responsibilities relating to the functions of the Office which the Secretary may assign, consistent with this chapter. Employees of the Office shall be recruited on the basis of their professional competence and capacity to administer the provisions of this chapter. The Office may use, on a reimbursable basis when appropriate, employees of the Department and other Federal agencies to administer the provisions of this chapter, providing that no legal authority, program, or function in any Federal agency which has as its purpose promoting the development or use of coal or other mineral resources or regulating the health and safety of miners under provisions of the Federal Coal Mine Health and Safety Act of 1969 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/83/742"},"text":"83 Stat. 742","children":[],"tail":") ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s801"},"text":"30 U.S.C. 801","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], shall be transferred to the Office."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id60317d45-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Duties of Secretary","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary, acting through the Office, shall—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d46-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" administer the programs for controlling surface coal mining operations which are required by this chapter; review and approve or disapprove State programs for controlling surface coal mining operations and reclaiming abandoned mined lands; make those investigations and inspections necessary to insure compliance with this chapter; conduct hearings, administer oaths, issue subpenas, and compel the attendance of witnesses and production of written or printed material as provided for in this chapter; issue cease-and-desist orders; review and vacate or modify or approve orders and decisions; and order the suspension, revocation, or withholding of any permit for failure to comply with any of the provisions of this chapter or any rules and regulations adopted pursuant thereto;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d47-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" publish and promulgate such rules and regulations as may be necessary to carry out the purposes and provisions of this chapter;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d48-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" administer the State grant-in-aid program for the development of State programs for surface and mining and reclamation operations provided for in subchapter V of this chapter;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d49-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" administer the program for the purchase and reclamation of abandoned and unreclaimed mined areas pursuant to subchapter IV of this chapter;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d4a-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" administer the surface mining and reclamation research and demonstration project authority provided for in this chapter;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d4b-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" consult with other agencies of the Federal Government having expertise in the control and reclamation of surface mining operations and assist States, local governments, and other eligible agencies in the coordination of such programs;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d4c-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" maintain a continuing study of surface mining and reclamation operations in the United States;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d4d-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" develop and maintain an Information and Data Center on Surface Coal Mining, Reclamation, and Surface Impacts of Underground Mining, which will make such data available to the public and the Federal, regional, State, and local agencies conducting or concerned with land use planning and agencies concerned with surface and underground mining and reclamation operations;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d4e-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"(9)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" assist the States in the development of State programs for surface coal mining and reclamation operations which meet the requirements of this chapter, and at the same time, reflect local requirements and local environmental and agricultural conditions;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d4f-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/10"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10"},"text":"(10)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" assist the States in developing objective scientific criteria and appropriate procedures and institutions for determining those areas of a State to be designated unsuitable for all or certain types of surface coal mining pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s1272"},"text":"section 1272 of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d50-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/11"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11"},"text":"(11)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" monitor all Federal and State research programs dealing with coal extraction and use and recommend to Congress the research and demonstration projects and necessary changes in public policy which are designated to (A) improve feasibility of underground coal mining, and (B) improve surface mining and reclamation techniques directed at eliminating adverse environmental and social impacts;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d51-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/12"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12"},"text":"(12)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" cooperate with other Federal agencies and State regulatory authorities to minimize duplication of inspections, enforcement, and administration of this chapter; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d52-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/c/13"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"13"},"text":"(13)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" perform such other duties as may be provided by law and relate to the purposes of this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id60317d53-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Restriction on use of Federal coal mine health and safety inspectors","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Director shall not use either permanently or temporarily any person charged with responsibility of inspecting coal mines under the Federal Coal Mine Health and Safety Act of 1969 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s801"},"text":"30 U.S.C. 801","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], unless he finds and publishes such finding in the Federal Register, that such activities would not interfere with such inspections under the 1969 Act."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id60317d54-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Repealed. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/511/s4/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–511, § 4(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-11"},"text":"Dec. 11, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2826"},"text":"94 Stat. 2826","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id60317d55-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Conflict of interest; penalties; rules and regulations; report to Congress","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No employee of the Office or any other Federal employee performing any function or duty under this chapter shall have a direct or indirect financial interest in underground or surface coal mining operations. Whoever knowingly violates the provisions of the above sentence shall, upon conviction, be punished by a fine of not more than $2,500, or by imprisonment for not more than one year, or both. The Director shall (1) within sixty days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-08-03"},"text":"August 3, 1977","children":[],"tail":", publish regulations, in accordance with "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s553"},"text":"section 553 of title 5","children":[],"tail":", to establish the methods by which the provisions of this subsection will be monitored and enforced, including appropriate provisions for the filing by such employees and the review of statements and supplements thereto concerning their financial interests which may be affected by this subsection, and (2) report to the Congress as part of the annual report ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s1296"},"text":"section 1296 of this title","children":[],"tail":") on the actions taken and not taken during the preceding calendar year under this subsection."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id60317d56-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Petition for issuance, amendment, or repeal of rule; filing; hearing or investigation; notice of denial","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d57-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/g/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" After the Secretary has adopted the regulations required by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s1251"},"text":"section 1251 of this title","children":[],"tail":", any person may petition the Director to initiate a proceeding for the issuance, amendment, or repeal of a rule under this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d58-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/g/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Such petitions shall be filed in the principal office of the Director and shall set forth the facts which it is claimed established that it is necessary to issue, amend, or repeal a rule under this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d59-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/g/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Director may hold a public hearing or may conduct such investigation or proceeding as the Director deems appropriate in order to determine whether or not such petition should be granted.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id60317d5a-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1211/g/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Within ninety days after filing of a petition described in paragraph (1), the Director shall either grant or deny the petition. If the Director grants such petition, the Director shall promptly commence an appropriate proceeding in accordance with the provisions of this chapter. If the Director denies such petition, the Director shall so notify the petitioner in writing setting forth the reasons for such denial.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id60317d5b-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/87/tII/s201"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–87, title II, § 201","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-08-03"},"text":"Aug. 3, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/449"},"text":"91 Stat. 449","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/240/tI/s100"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–240, title I, § 100","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-03-07"},"text":"Mar. 7, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/109"},"text":"92 Stat. 109","children":[],"tail":"; 1978 Reorg. Plan No. 2, § 102, eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", 43 F.R. 36037, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/3783"},"text":"92 Stat. 3783","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/511/s4/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–511, § 4(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-11"},"text":"Dec. 11, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2826"},"text":"94 Stat. 2826","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id60317d5c-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id60317d5d-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id60317d5e-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Coal Mine Health and Safety Act of 1969, referred to in subsecs. (b) and (d), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/173"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–173","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1969","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/83/742"},"text":"83 Stat. 742","children":[],"tail":", which was redesignated the Federal Mine Safety and Health Act of 1977 by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/164/tI/s101"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–164, title I, § 101","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-11-09"},"text":"Nov. 9, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/1290"},"text":"91 Stat. 1290","children":[],"tail":", and is classified principally to chapter 22 (§ 801 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s801"},"text":"section 801 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id60317d5f-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/511"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–511","children":[],"tail":" struck subsec. (e) which provided for consideration of Office of Surface Mining Reclamation and Enforcement as an independent Federal regulatory agency. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t44/s3502/10"},"text":"section 3502(10) of Title 44","children":[],"tail":", Public Printing and Documents."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/240"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–240","children":[],"tail":" substituted “V” for “IV”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id60317d60-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id60317d61-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1980 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/511"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–511","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-04-01"},"text":"Apr. 1, 1981","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/511/s5"},"text":"section 5 of Pub. L. 96–511","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t44/s2904"},"text":"section 2904 of Title 44","children":[],"tail":", Public Printing and Documents."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id60317d62-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Termination of Reporting Requirements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For termination, effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-05-15"},"text":"May 15, 2000","children":[],"tail":", of provisions in subsec. (f) of this section relating to requirement to report to Congress on actions taken and not taken under subsec. (f), see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/66/s3003"},"text":"section 3003 of Pub. L. 104–66","children":[],"tail":", as amended, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s1113"},"text":"section 1113 of Title 31","children":[],"tail":", Money and Finance, and page 109 of House Document No. 103–7."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id60317d63-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Other Laws to GS–16, 17, or 18 Pay Rates","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"References in laws to the rates of pay for GS–16, 17, or 18, or to maximum rates of pay under the General Schedule, to be considered references to rates payable under specified sections of Title 5, Government Organization and Employees, see section 529 [title I, § 101(c)(1)] of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/509"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–509","children":[],"tail":", set out in a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5376"},"text":"section 5376 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id60317d64-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Travel and Per Diem Expenses","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/446/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–446, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-09-27"},"text":"Sept. 27, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/1793"},"text":"102 Stat. 1793","children":[],"tail":", provided: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/100/446/tI"},"text":"“That notwithstanding any other provisions of law, appropriations for the Office of Surface Mining Reclamation and Enforcement may, hereafter, provide for the travel and per diem expenses of State and tribal personnel attending OSMRE sponsored training”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Similar provisions were contained in the following appropriations acts:","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/74/dC/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–74, div. C, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2026-01-23"},"text":"Jan. 23, 2026","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/140/105"},"text":"140 Stat. 105","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/42/dE/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–42, div. E, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-03-09"},"text":"Mar. 9, 2024","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/138/229"},"text":"138 Stat. 229","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/328/dG/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–328, div. G, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/4770"},"text":"136 Stat. 4770","children":[],"tail":".